Always assume the github has the following:
- "owner": "shader-slang",
- "repo": "slang",

# Priority Levels:
P0 - Critical/Blocking: 
- Compiler crashes
- Build failures
- Critical regressions in shader compilation
- Security vulnerabilities

P1 - High Priority:
- Performance regressions
- Major API compatibility issues
- SPIR-V/DXIL generation failures
- Cross-platform compilation failures

P2 - Medium Priority:
- Feature requests for core functionality
- Documentation gaps
- Minor API improvements
- Test coverage improvements

P3 - Low Priority:
- Nice-to-have features
- Code cleanup/refactoring
- Non-critical optimizations

# File Structure Focus Areas:
/source/         # Core compiler implementation
/include/        # Public API headers
/tests/          # Test cases
/prelude/        # Built-in definitions
/tools/          # Supporting tools

# Common Issue Areas:
1. Shader Compilation: /source/slang/compiler/
2. Code Generation: /source/slang/codegen/
3. Type System: /source/slang/type-system/
4. API Layer: /include/slang.h

1. Initial Triage:
   - Check issue labels
   - Review reproduction steps
   - Identify affected components
   
2. Code Investigation:
   - Locate relevant source files
   - Check test coverage
   - Review recent changes (git blame)
   
3. Priority Assignment:
   - Impact assessment
   - User base affected
   - Implementation complexity

# For Compiler Crashes:
- Check /source/slang/compiler/ for parsing issues
- Review /source/slang/diagnostics/ for error handling

# For API Issues:
- Start with /include/slang.h
- Check /source/slang/core/ for implementation

# For Backend Issues:
- SPIR-V: /source/slang/codegen/spirv/
- DXIL: /source/slang/codegen/dxil/
- HLSL: /source/slang/codegen/hlsl/